<a href="/nu/" class="province-card"><span class="flag">🇨🇦</span><span class="name">Nunavut</span><span class="tag status-soon">Coming soon</span></a>
</div>
</section>

<section class="features">
<h2>What you'll find in each guide</h2>
<div class="feature-list">
<div class="feature-card">
<h3>⚡ On-the-Ground Response</h3>
<p>What to say and do immediately when denied access. Read it on your phone at the door.</p>
</div>
<div class="feature-card">
<h3>⚖️ Legal Basis</h3>
<p>The actual laws that protect your right to enter with your service animal.</p>
</div>
<div class="feature-card">
<h3>📋 Key Definitions</h3>
<p>Who is protected, what animals qualify, and what staff can legally ask.</p>
</div>
<div class="feature-card">
<h3>📝 Recourse</h3>
<p>Exactly how to file a complaint, deadlines, and templates you can use.</p>
</div>
<div class="feature-card">
<h3>🔍 Context &amp; Nuances</h3>
<p>Exceptions, responsibilities, and practical details for real situations.</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<footer>
<p>Based on provincial and territorial human rights legislation. This is not legal advice.</p>
<p>Service Animal Access Guide — serviceanimal.ca</p>
</footer>
</body>
</html>
